# Import direction

```
routes → handlers → { core, services, database, factories, utils }
core → { services, database, factories, utils }
services → { database, factories, utils }
workers → { core, services, database, factories, utils }
addon → handlers
middleware → { utils }   (and constants/types as needed)
```

**`utils`** and **`factories`** are leaf layers — no imports from handlers, core, services, or database upward.

## Layer roles

| Layer | Role |
| --- | --- |
| `routes/` | Thin Express routers — delegate to handlers |
| `middleware/` | Cross-cutting HTTP (auth, rate limits, headers, logging) |
| `handlers/` | REST and Stremio entry — orchestrate lower layers |
| `core/` | Queue, scheduler, prefetch jobs, SSE broadcasters, room lifecycle |
| `services/` | Outbound HTTP (`axios`); normalize at the API boundary |
| `factories/` | Pure mappers — no I/O |
| `database/` | PostgreSQL SQL only — one `pool.query` (or `client.query` in transaction) per function |
| `utils/` | Small pure helpers |
| `workers/` | Child-process entry for prefetch sync only |
| `addon/` | Stremio `addonBuilder` handler registration |

## Do not

- **`services` → `core`** or **`core` → `handlers`**
- **`database` → `services`** or **`database` → `core`**
- **`factories` → `database`** or **`factories` → `services`**
- **`axios`** outside **`services/`** (except rare one-off in a handler)
- Import **`src/temp/`**
- Add parallel top-level **`sdk/`** or **`scheduler/`** — use **`src/addon/`** and **`src/core/`**
- Put **`pool.query`** in **`factories/`**, **`handlers`** in **`core/`**, or business orchestration that belongs in **`core/`** inside **`handlers/`**

Details: [`addon-layering.mdc`](addon-layering.mdc)
